-- Gamesa Climbs 7% in Madrid Trading, Biggest Gain in Month, on Broker Buys
-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e   a n d   B e n   S i l l s
-- 2010-12-10T12:27:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-10/gamesa-climbs-7-in-madrid-trading-biggest-gain-in-month-on-broker-buys.html
Gamesa Corporacion Tecnologica SA,
Spain’s biggest wind-turbine manufacturer, rose the most in a
month as brokers Morgan Stanley and Espirito Santo Investment
acquired stakes worth a combined 4.8 million euros
($6.4 million).  The company’s shares rose as much as 35 cents and traded at
5.42 euros, up 6.9 percent, as of 1:24 p.m. local time.  Morgan Stanley was the largest buyer, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Todd White at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  